Hi what are your first impressions of the movie?
Hello! What movie would that be?
The Shape of Water, It gets high ratings from every source
That's an interesting name. Is it a science-based movie?
Fantasy drama with some science fiction more than science
Good cast , although not big names
Science fiction works perfectly too! It makes most movies better
Really? It's nice to see movies give newer or less known actors a shot.
It certainly can make them more entertaining
Director is pretty famous , although I am not very familiar with his work
What's the director's name?
Guillermo del Toro
Oh, wow. Yeah, he's a pretty good director. I thought he only made horror/thriller movies
The story revolves around a mute cleaning woman at a government facility in Baltimore
That doesn't sound like a good thing for that woman.
It sounds like she's going to witness something she shouldn't have
She falls in love with an amphibian humanoid creature being held there
Well, that doesn't sound nearly as bad as I was expecting
She rescues the creature from the facility and keeps him in her bath tub
That sounds like a bad move. Does the facility trace it back to her?
Eventually. Her neighbor helps her conceal him and they discover that the creature has healing abilities
It sounds like a pretty bad movie to earn best picture
It definitely sounds like a B-rated movie, but you can't judge a book by its cover
G del Toro does a pretty good job of adding emotions and unexpected twists in his movie
They take the creature to the canal to release it when the officials start looking for it
The way you phrased that makes it sound like they don't succeed in the attempt.
She and the creature get shot but the creature heals itself and dives into the canal with her .  It heals her and gives her gills so they can live together underwater.
On one hand I enjoy that happy ending, on another I'm fairly disappointed they lived.
I'm not sure what I think of the ending
Not sure I would recommend the movie but it is probably good enough to watch
There's a moderate chance that ending is just the dying fantasy of the creature and woman. He likes to leave hints for the viewers to go through if they want
Yeah, it would be nice to watch on a day where you're just relaxing
Thanks for your views. Have a good day
Anytime! You too

uid1response.feedback: It's a possible movie to watch with my friends during our next movie night.
